": "Thymus x citriodorus", "slug": "thymus-x-citriodorus", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Mediterranean. Natural hybrid of T. vulgaris and T. pulegioides.", "traits": "Small shrub 15-30cm tall, spreading 30-45cm. Oval dark green leaves. Pink to lavender flowers in mid-summer. Distinct citrus scent.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good to excellent. Vigorous once established.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Thymus serpyllum / Thymus praecox", "slug": "thymus-serpyllum-thymus-praecox", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Europe, North Africa. Ancient heirloom variety cultivated for thousands of years.", "traits": "Very low-growing (2-8cm), mat-forming groundcover. Tiny oval leaves, dense growth. Profuse magenta-pink to purple flowers in summer. Spreads 30-60cm.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate for culinary use, excellent as ornamental groundcover.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Available at Brisbane garden centers including specialist nurseries. The Seed Collection Australia offers seeds.", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Thymus x citriodorus ''Lime''", "slug": "thymus-x-citriodorus-lime", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Cultivar selection from lemon thyme group.", "traits": "Chartreuse to light green foliage, 15-25cm tall. Compact growth. Pale pink flowers.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good. Regular producer.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Specialty herb nurseries, selected Brisbane garden centers.", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Thymus vulgaris ''Orange Balsam''", "slug": "thymus-vulgaris-orange-balsam", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Selected cultivar from common thyme.", "traits": "Neat, small upright shrub 10-30cm. Narrow orange-scented leaves, gray-green. Lavender flowers.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate. Compact growth limits harvest volume.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Specialty herb suppliers, online nurseries.", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "Thymus herba-barona", "slug": "thymus-herba-barona", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Sardinia and Corsica. Traditionally used to flavor ''Baron of Beef'' roasts.", "traits": "Low-growing 10-15cm, spreading mat. Narrow dark green leaves. Small pinkish-purple flowers. Strong caraway scent from carvone compound.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate. Dense growth provides good coverage.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Specialty herb nurseries, online suppliers.", "sort_order": 7}, {"name": "Thymus ''Silver Queen'' (Lemon Thyme)", "slug": "thymus-silver-queen-lemon-thyme", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Selected variegated cultivar. Award of Garden Merit winner (Royal Horticultural Society).", "traits": "Bushy dwarf 22-30cm tall, spreading 37-45cm. Small ovate dark green leaves edged in silver. Pale mauve flowers. Ornamental value.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good. Attractive garnish option.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 8}, {"name": "Thymus citriodorus ''Doone Valley''", "slug": "thymus-citriodorus-doone-valley", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Selected variegated lemon thyme cultivar.", "traits": "Mat-forming, 5-10cm tall, spreading 30-60cm. Dark green leaves heavily marked with gold, developing copper-red tones in cold. Lavender-pink flowers.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate. Ornamental value high.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Specialty nurseries, online herb suppliers.", "sort_order": 9}, {"name": "Thymus pseudolanuginosus", "slug": "thymus-pseudolanuginosus", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Europe. Ornamental selection.", "traits": "Very low-growing 2-5cm, spreading mat to 60cm. Gray-green leaves covered in fine white hairs giving fuzzy texture. Pale pink flowers (sparse).", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Low for culinary purposes. Excellent groundcover.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Selected Brisbane garden centers, specialist groundcover nurseries.", "sort_order": 10}, {"name": "Thymus serpyllum ''Pink Chintz''", "slug": "thymus-serpyllum-pink-chintz", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Selected ornamental creeping thyme.", "traits": "Mat-forming 2-5cm tall, spreading 45cm. Fuzzy olive-green to dark green foliage. Salmon-pink to magenta flowers in early spring. First thyme to flower.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Low culinary. Excellent ornamental.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Brisbane garden centers, groundcover specialists.", "sort_order": 11}, {"name": "Thymus serpyllum ''Elfin'' / Thymus praecox ''Elfin''", "slug": "thymus-serpyllum-elfin-thymus-praecox-elfin", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Selected miniature cultivar.", "traits": "Tiniest thyme variety, 1-3cm tall, spreading 10-20cm slowly. Minute glossy green leaves. Sparse lavender-pink flowers. Moss-like appearance.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Minimal. Ornamental fairy gardens, rock gardens.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Specialty nurseries, online miniature plant suppliers.", "sort_order": 12}, {"name": "Thymus pulegioides cv. Pennsylvania Dutch", "slug": "thymus-pulegioides-cv-pennsylvania-dutch", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Pennsylvania Dutch heritage variety, USA. Traditional tea herb.", "traits": "Larger oval dark green leaves than most thymes. Upright growth to 30cm. Strong scent. Semi-shrub form.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Excellent for tea production. Larger leaves easier to harvest.", "growing_notes": 